<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:50PM EDT  by NWS Tallahassee</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Irwin
and Berrien Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 450 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alapaha, or 10 miles south of Ocilla, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Nashville, Ocilla, Enigma, Alapaha, Berrien Co A/P, Gladys, Weber,
Glory, Wray and Bannockburn.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
